{
  "title": "Packaging Data Pipelines Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides a comprehensive overview of creating and packaging data pipelines utilizing FastAPI, a modern web framework for building APIs in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI is designed to simplify the process of building efficient, scalable, and secure APIs.",
    "Python 3.12+ is required to leverage its latest features such as pattern matching and improved type hints.",
    "Data pipelines are composed by organizing multiple endpoints that perform specific tasks, handling data processing, validation, and transformation.",
    "FastAPI supports multiple backends for databases and message queues like SQLAlchemy, Motor (MongoDB), Redis, RabbitMQ, etc.",
    "The API can be packaged as a standalone application or integrated with other services using the FastAPI Uvicorn and HyperFastAPIRunner ASGI servers.",
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.get('/')\ndef root():\n    return {'message': 'Hello World!'}"
    },
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "from pydantic import BaseModel\nclass Item(BaseModel):\n    name: str\n    description: str\n@app.post('/items/')\ndef create_item(item: Item):\n    return item"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required to leverage its latest features such as pattern matching and improved type hints.",
    "FastAPI v0.68.0 introduces the concept of Dependency Injection, which allows developers to use their own custom dependencies.",
    "Uvicorn v0.15.0 brings significant performance improvements and better handling of exceptions."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Ensure that you install FastAPI as a production dependency instead of developing with it installed in the editable mode.",
    "FastAPI doesn't provide an ORM, but it can be easily integrated with existing ORMs like SQLAlchemy or Motor (for MongoDB).",
    "It is essential to follow best practices for API design and security when building data pipelines."
  ]
}
